{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"lhba46lu14mpydc48injol4","title":"Raspberrypi","desc":"Raspberry Pi Setup Notes","updated":1654404734179,"created":1647065899204,"custom":{},"fname":"devnotes.raspberrypi","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"451eb07e62e1898285526a8a9bad55a9","links":[],"anchors":{"general-info":{"type":"header","text":"General Info","value":"general-info","line":7,"column":0,"depth":2},"home-assistant-container-installation":{"type":"header","text":"Home Assistant Container Installation","value":"home-assistant-container-installation","line":13,"column":0,"depth":2},"docker-commands":{"type":"header","text":"Docker Commands","value":"docker-commands","line":26,"column":0,"depth":2},"general-rpi-commands":{"type":"header","text":"General RPI Commands","value":"general-rpi-commands","line":35,"column":0,"depth":2},"how-to-reset-dhcp-settings":{"type":"header","text":"How to Reset DHCP Settings","value":"how-to-reset-dhcp-settings","line":43,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["km3p1117axuqmoj2zjbwstu"],"parent":"lcTujcWsxBfPEpzP49YbQ","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"raspberrypi\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#raspberrypi\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Raspberrypi</h1>\n<h2 id=\"general-info\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#general-info\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>General Info</h2>\n<p>Getting the installation of Home Assistant and PiHole was a pain. This is not a good note.</p>\n<p>Was easiest to do the install with Docker Compose, my router from AT&#x26;T does not accept custom DNS so I had to use the PiHole as a DHCP Server. Had to modify the docker compose file and add a couple environmental variables to make it work. Will document these tomorrow.</p>\n<h2 id=\"home-assistant-container-installation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#home-assistant-container-installation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Home Assistant Container Installation</h2>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">docker</span> run -d <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --name homeassistant <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --privileged <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --restart<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>unless-stopped <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  -e <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">TZ</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>America/Los_Angeles <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  -v /home/pi/homeassistant <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --network<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>host <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  ghcr.io/home-assistant/home-assistant:stable\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"docker-commands\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#docker-commands\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Docker Commands</h2>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">docker</span> container <span class=\"token function\">ls</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">docker</span> container <span class=\"token function\">rm</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$CONTAINER_NAME</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">docker</span> image <span class=\"token function\">ls</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">docker</span> image <span class=\"token function\">rm</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$IMAGE_ID</span>\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"general-rpi-commands\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#general-rpi-commands\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>General RPI Commands</h2>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> rfkill block wifi\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> rfkill block bluetooth\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> rfkill unblock wifi\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-reset-dhcp-settings\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#how-to-reset-dhcp-settings\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>How to Reset DHCP Settings</h2>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">service</span> dhcpcd status\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">service</span> dhcpcd start\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> systemctl <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">enable</span> dhcpcd\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">nano</span> /etc/dhcpcd.conf\n</code></pre>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/DevNotes/notes/km3p1117axuqmoj2zjbwstu\">RaspberryPi Pi-Hole</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"root","desc":"","updated":1605266684036,"created":1595961348801,"stub":false,"custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"cf4622cd4e7841f93fb3051e6203c8e6","links":[],"anchors":{},"children":["uRNDWirv66xgHSdrPwMcw","lcTujcWsxBfPEpzP49YbQ","FTV8hEHhyid0DiEvv9gNj","ph4ta0hoi7x0vch4uoz72hn","boufkx25rro7ysodpanan5g","01u0co3RYjOM1bjpc2qIU","xt9womgr90xi5ui5nezev7b","qpngd6ap92mmahr4bh4gc47","hobifg8vvmmg17kt2z5p36a"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nThis is the root for your Dendron vault.\n\nIf you decide to publish your entire vault, it will be your landing page. You are free to customize any part of this page except the frontmatter at the top, between the `---`. \n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"